= Useful tools =

 * Ben Gamari has a bunch of handy, albeit sometimes poorly documented, tools in his [[http://github.com/bgamari/ghc-utils|ghc-utils]] repository.
 * Joachim Breitner has developed the lovely [[http://github.com/nomeata/gipeda|gipeda]] web interface for comparing performance metrics between commits. This powers [[http://perf.haskell.org/|perf.haskell.org]] (with data from Joachim's [[http://github.com/nomeata/ghc-speed-logs|ghc-speed-logs]] repository
 * Ben Gamari has developed a set of [[http://github.com/bgamari/ghc-perf-import|tools]] for slurping the `ghc-speed-logs` data into a PostgreSQL database and do interesting timeseries analyses on it.